suppress.notes: CVE is a json vulnerability for Node projects. False positive reported at https://github.com/jeremylong/DependencyCheck/issues/2794
file name: snakeyaml-1.33.jar SnakeYaml's Constructor() class does not restrict types which can be instantiated during deserialization

file name: spring-security-crypto-5.7.6.jar Spring Security versions 5.3.x prior to 5.3.2, 5.2.x prior to 5.2.4, 5.1.x prior to 5.1.10, 5.0.x prior to 5.0.16 and 4.2.x prior to 4.2.16 use a fixed null initialization vector with CBC Mode in the implementation of the queryable text encryptor. A malicious user with access to the data that has been encrypted using such an encryptor may be able to derive the unencrypted values using a dictionary attack.
file name: spring-web-5.3.24.jar Pivotal Spring Framework through 5.3.16 suffers from a potential remote code execution (RCE) issue if used for Java deserialization of untrusted data
